description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;PLEASE NOTE THIS VACANCY IS WITHIN NHS WALES DELIVERY UNIT AND NOT SWANSEA BAY ULHB&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note this secondment opportunity is open to NHS Wales staff from all Health Boards in Wales only&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting secondment opportunity has arisen within NHS Wales Delivery unit for a Quality and Safety Manager. The successful candidate will work closely with the Assistant Director of Quality &amp; Safety to provide clinical leadership for the quality agenda across the system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a clinical qualification, experience of managing quality governance and effective influencing and negotiating skills, you will as part of the team drive change and improvements for quality and safety across Wales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you believe you have the skills and motivation to help us drive continuous quality improvement and service transformation and would like to know more about this role, please contact Sally Pearson, EA to Julie McCabe, Assistant Director Quality &amp; Safety sally.pearson@wales.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Wrexham in North Wales or Pencoed in South Wales ( home working as per guidance).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working Hours: 22.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Secondment Period: December 2020 to June 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note you will need to have your line manager’s approval to undertake the secondment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sally PearsonExecutive Assistant/Business Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;sally.pearson@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Sally Pearson via email for further details of this post, due to working at home guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
